            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We also find structures that change in a different way…",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 41,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER3",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can explore this with lamin B1—a protein that forms a mesh cage on the inside of the nuclear envelope— and the endoplasmic reticulum (ER).",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 42,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER4",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "push",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "Disassembly & Recompartmentalization",
                        "element": "h3",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 43,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER5",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "The nuclear envelope is a structure that disassembles during mitosis. During this process, lamin B1 appears as a solid shell which then becomes ruffled and billows out.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 44,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER6",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "By comparing the localization pattern of lamin B1 with that of other structures using our Integrated Mitotic Stem Cell model, we notice that it mirrors the structure and behavior of the ER during mitosis.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 45,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "two-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER7",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "This could be explained by the fact that lamin B1 is a membrane associated protein and that the outer nuclear membrane is contiguous with the ER.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 46,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER8",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We can see the association of laminB1 with the ER during mitosis more clearly by using dual-edited cell lines.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 47,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER9",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "In addition to the nuclear envelope and the ER we notice other structures that disassemble and recompartmentalize.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 48,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER10",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "These include the Golgi apparatus…",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 49,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "ER11",
                "loop": false,
                "advanceOnExit": false
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "These include the Golgi apparatus and the nucleolus.",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "pageId": 50,
            "transition": "",
            "layout": "one-column",
            "media": {
                "mediaId": "main-movie",
                "marker": "TJ1",
                "loop": true,
                "advanceOnExit": true
            },
            "body": {
                "transition": "stack",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "text": "We have described structures that change during mitosis. Do any structures stay te same?",
                        "element": "p",
                        "type": "text"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
}